The paper presents a machine learning model for improving the performance of linear neural networks, specifically in the context of Few-Shot learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with interpretability, which is a common concern in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The model is tested on image datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a linear function for each class in the dataset suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
